# spark-benchmark

Reproducible local-LLM benchmark harness for **NVIDIA DGX Spark only** (v1).
v1 is intentionally Spark-only — never frame results as cross-platform comparisons.

## v1 lineup (canonical)

- `qwen-3.6` (Ollama tag `qwen3.6:35b`)
- `gemma-4` (Ollama tag `gemma4:31b`)
- `nemotron-3` (Ollama tag `nemotron3:33b`)
- `nemotron-3-super` is **retired** — its YAML is a tombstone, do not re-add it.

## Production backend

Ollama HTTP at `http://localhost:11434/api/generate`. `llamacpp` adapter exists; `trt-llm` / `vllm` are stubs.

## Run commands (always with `PYTHONPATH=src`)

```bash
PYTHONPATH=src python3 -m spark_benchmark.cli wizard \
  --experiment configs/experiments/spark-ollama-baseline.yaml --platform spark

PYTHONPATH=src python3 -m spark_benchmark.cli benchmark \
  otestuj qwen gemma nemotron zamer se na rychlost spolehlivost \
  --experiment configs/experiments/spark-ollama-baseline.yaml --platform spark
```

NL parser understands Czech + English keywords (`rychlost`/`speed`,
`spolehliv`/`reliab`, `kod`/`code`, `dlouhodob`/`sustained`, `openclaw`).

## Results layout (do not change shape lightly)

```
results/benchmarks/<run-id>/
├─ plan.json
└─ <suite>/{manifest.json, results.jsonl, summary.json, summary.md}
```

Run IDs come from `results_bundle.make_run_id()` (`YYYYMMDDTHHMMSSZ-<8hex>`).

For full module map see `docs/architecture.md`. For planned suites see
`docs/extensions-spec.md`. Methodology lives in `METHODOLOGY.md` — keep it
honest: publish failures, not just wins.
